      • normalize

        public void normalize()
        Description copied from interface: IVector
        Sets the length of this vector to a single unit length. For example, A(2,5) becomes A(1,1), B(-5,0) becomes B(-1,0). This isn't the proper normalization of a real vector since this only uses integers.
